children.text: There is a bend down the face of the door, which is stopping the door closing up tightly to the frame.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances clause 8.05 Distortion of Doors, states that
‘Door leaves are defective if, during the initial three months they twist or bend greater than the limits listed in Table 8.05’ .
This door and/or the frame it is fitted into will need to be properly rectified so that the door can close up tight to the frame.
